commitMessage:

The implementation was done with a combination of ifdefs and contacts
service API emulation. The default is to build the plugin for contacts
service.

An EDS with the new Cursor API is needed.

See src/Contact/contacts2ebook/README for more information about
design choices, usage and limitations.

Patch Set 2:

to answer the question about the need for a run time dependency...

This patch is depending on libebook instead of just directly making dbus calls, so it's the libebook library responsibility to add an explicit rpm 'Requires:' since rpmbuild has no way of auto detecting the dependency.

If this isnt' happening then please file a bug and fix the other package.

Patch Set 2:

Baptiste, libebook is packaged together with the corresponding daemon, so everything will be pulled in as needed when installing the wrt plugin compiled for EDS.

This packaging of EDS is the same as the one of the contacts service.

I'm not saying that this is ideal. But that is a separate discussion that we should have on the Tizen dev mailing list, so I am not going to expand on it here.
